 preference shares on the borsa italiana in  a reorganisation of the agnelli familys holdings in  led to the merger of ifi and ifil to create exor the new name being taken from the french company then the majority owner of perrier water and the château margaux estate which it acquired in  the family firm giovanni agnelli bv owns  of the share capital exor is ranked th largest company by revenue according to the  and  fortune global  lists mergers shares and acquisitionsedit partnerreedit in  exor bought partnerre with a bid of  per share total  billions originally it had offered  per share and in response axis re offered  per share in paper plus  in a preclosing dividend the economistedit on august   the editor announced that exor will purchase threefifths of the economist group shares currently owned by pearson plc exor held shares in the economist group prior to this purchase this is considered to be the most important change to the economists shareholding structure in almost  years pearson plc which also owns the financial times has had a noncontrolling  stake in the economist group since  the economist group will buy back the remained twofifths of pearson shares cushman  wakefieldedit on september   exor closed the sale of cushman  wakefield to chicagobased dtz for  billion in net generating a capital gain of  million for the holding company of italys agnelli family board of directorsedit board of directors in charge as of  august  john philip elkann  chairman and chief executive officer sergio marchionne  vice chairman alessandro nasi di villapaciosa  vice chairman andrea agnelli  director marc bolland  independent director niccolò camerana  director ginevra elkann  director annemiek fentener van vlissingen  independent director jae yong lee  independent director antonio mota de sousa hortaosorio  independent director vittorio avogadro di collobiano  director lupo rattazzi  director robert speyer  independent director mike volpi  lead independent director ruthi